article.description:
Olympia Scott-Richardson made two free
throws with 3.6 seconds remaining Monday night to lift the Indiana
Fever to a 73-72 victory over the Charlotte Sting.
article.headline: Indiana comes through with clutch plays
article.linkText: Big free throws, big 3-pointer lift Fever past Sting
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Olympia Scott-Richardson made two free
throws with 3.6 seconds remaining Monday night to lift the Indiana
Fever to a 73-72 victory over the Charlotte Sting.

	   Tamika Catchings and Nikki McCray scored 17 points each for
Indiana (9-13), which snapped a four-game losing skid.

	   Dawn Staley scored 14 points and Allison Feaster 13 for
Charlotte (13-9), which lost for the first time in five games. The
Sting fell two games behind idle Washington in the race for the
Eastern Conference lead.

	   The game went back and forth in the last 54 seconds after
Feaster made a 3-pointer and two free throws to fuel a 9-2 run over
a 2:21 span. Sting center Tammy Sutton-Brown capped the rally by
hitting a layup for a 69-68 lead.

	   ''We did a good job holding them after they made their run,''
Scott-Richardson said. ''We know we have the ability to play like
this.''

	   With the Fever out of timeouts, Catchings missed a driving shot,
but grabbed the rebound and fed the ball to McCray, who hit a
25-footer from the middle for a 71-69 lead with 25.8 seconds
remaining.

	   ''It was a broken play,'' McCray said. ''We wanted Tamika to get
to the foul line. Somebody tipped it. I didn't see what happened.
The ball came out to me and I just picked it up and shot it.''

	   Erin Buescher sank a 3-pointer from the top of the key with 13.5
seconds to go. Catchings drove down the lane into a crowd and
missed the shot, but Scott-Richardson grabbed the rebound and was
fouled by Sutton-Brown.

	   ''We had some big 3s,'' Fever coach Nell Fortner said. ''Nikki
hit a big 3 at the end of the game, and Niele Ivey had a big 3. At
the beginning of the season, we were doing that. The bench was
really important. We've got to get that back.''

	   Sting coach Anne Donovan gave the Fever credit for 
aggressiveness.

	   ''We hit that huge 3,'' she said of Buescher's shot. ''Indiana
didn't have any timeouts. They had to scramble for the shot.

	   ''Indiana was great tonight. They were aggressive from start to
finish.''
